Here's the XAML and ViewModel pattern:

## XAML

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="Auto,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}" WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Name}" VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

## ViewModel Bindings

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    public ObservableCollection<Item> Items { get; } = new();

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelected()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"detail?id={CurrentItem.Id}");

        // Clear selection so user can re-select the same item later
        CurrentItem = null;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task Refresh()
    {
        var data = await _apiService.GetItemsAsync();
        Items.Clear();
        foreach (var item in data)
            Items.Add(item);

        IsRefreshing = false; // Stops the refresh spinner
    }
}
```

## Key Points

| Binding | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `IsRefreshing` (TwoWay) | Controls the refresh spinner; set `false` when done |
| `Command` on RefreshView | Fires your `RefreshCommand` on pull-down |
| `SelectedItem` (TwoWay) | Tracks the selected item in your ViewModel |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | Triggers navigation when selection changes |

**Important:**
- Use `ObservableCollection<T>` (not `List<T>`) so the UI updates on add/remove.
- Set `CurrentItem = null` after navigating so the same item can be re-selected.
- Set `IsRefreshing = false` at the end of your refresh logic to dismiss the spinner.
- Never use `ViewCell` inside the template — use `Grid`, `StackLayout`, etc.
